 I was high apprehensive (Kandim Firepot would talk to me and gave me the gear for Fear).  I turned in the note to the Barbarian chick and poof, Mr. Wizard pops.  My partner opened the trade window with the gnarled staff, I invised him... he clicked trade.  Mr. Wizard did not respond in any way (this is a good thing).  Then I (I was not invis) turned in my two staffs and presto chango a big bag in my inventory, exp chimes and what not.<br><br>You'll be nervous, I certainly was.  But it's MQ'able just like most stuff in the game.  Just use the invis trick.  Make sure your partner fully understands what he is doing before you do the quest.  And make sure you have enough faction to get the gear from gnome-boy Firepot.<br><br>Epic OWNS... quad kiting is a breeze, can run right past crap and it can't hit you.  You will often here me yelling, na-na-a-boo-boo you can't hit me, as I quad raptors around Timirous Deep.  That and I make a great tank for faction building in Kael Drakkel, we killed non stop with a warrior, bard, sk and me...  yes I was the tank, 800 hps is more than enough to keep the giants at bay.  No one ever needed a heal, it was great fun.<br><br>Anyway, I've digressed (can't help it, our epic is stellar).  You can MQ the SotF, just be careful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=1978.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=1978.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1978.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswiz